Explanation:

We iterate through the input arrays and merge the linked lists by comparing the values of the nodes. If the current node's value is smaller, we update the current node and move to the next node in the input array. Otherwise, we update the next node and move to the next node in the input array. Finally, we return the head node of the merged linked list.

The time complexity is O(n) because we only iterate through the input arrays once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space to store the head node of the merged linked list. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not require any additional energy consumption.

